Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.29,0:02:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的先祖依靠的是月亮與星星為時間分段時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors marked the passage of time by the Moon and stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.39,0:02:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,可在大約5000年前 在這裏生活過的人們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it was the people who once lived here, around 5,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.29,0:02:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,他們開始把時間分為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who first starting chopping up time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.13,0:02:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,小時和分鐘這樣更小的部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into smaller bite-sized portions of hours and minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.03,0:02:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,當時這個地方叫做烏魯克\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They call this place Uruk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.46,0:02:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在稱之為伊拉克\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We call it Iraq.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.50,0:02:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏是位於底格里斯河與幼發拉底河之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a part of Mesopotamia,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.24,0:02:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,美索不達米亞平原的一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the land between the Tigris and the Euphrates rivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.31,0:03:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,人們在這裏創建了城市\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The city was invented here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.35,0:03:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,在與時間無盡的戰鬥中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And one of humanity's greatest victories was won
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.91,0:03:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,取得了人類歷史上一個偉大的成就\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the ceaseless battle against time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.35,0:03:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,人類在這裏學會了如何書寫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was here that we learned how to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.39,0:03:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,死亡再也不能讓人默默無聞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Death could no longer silence us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.69,0:03:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,書寫給予了人類力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And writing gave us the power
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.72,0:03:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們可以逾越千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to reach across the millennia
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.83,0:03:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,與古人交流精神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and speak inside the heads of the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.56,0:03:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,歷史上沒有人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No one has ever spoken
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.83,0:03:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,能穿越如此之長的時間之河\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}across a longer stretch of time's river
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,除了阿卡德帝國的公主\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than this Akkadian princess,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.70,0:03:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,她是歷史上第一位君王的女兒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}daughter of the first emperor in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.17,0:03:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,也被稱為月亮公主——恩西杜安娜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and priestess of the Moon-- Enheduanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.41,0:03:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,她不僅僅會寫詩歌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For not only did she write poetry,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.88,0:03:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,恩西杜安娜還做了其他一些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but Enheduanna did something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.04,0:03:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,前人沒有做過的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no one before her had ever done--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.68,0:03:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,她在作品上署上自己的名字\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}she signed her name to her work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.22,0:03:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,可以說 她是歷史上第一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She's the first person for whom we can say
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.42,0:03:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我們知道確切身份\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we know who she was,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.39,0:03:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,也知道她的夢想世界的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and what she dreamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,她一直夢想著能走進神奇之門\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She dreamt of stepping through the Gate of Wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.23,0:03:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是恩西杜安娜所想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here's a thought Enheduanna sent
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.93,0:03:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,它穿越了4000年的時光來到我們身邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}across more than 4,000 years to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.93,0:04:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,下面就是她的作品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's from her work entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.47,0:04:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,名為《小女雄心》\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Lady of the Largest Heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.11,0:04:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,英娜娜 天上的金星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Innana, the planet Venus,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.78,0:04:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,愛的女神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}goddess of love, will have a great destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.15,0:04:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你是宇宙偉大的主宰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}throughout the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.22,0:04:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的主宰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...throughout the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.12,0:04:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,烏魯克也是史詩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And Uruk is also the place where the epic tale
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.96,0:04:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,《英雄的旅程》首次創作的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of "The Hero's Journey" was first written down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.49,0:04:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,遠在蝙蝠俠 天行者盧克\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Before Batman, Luke Skywalker,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.30,0:04:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,奧德賽——這些英雄誕生之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Odysseus-- before them all--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.40,0:04:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,傳說有一個人叫吉爾伽美什\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there was a man named Gilgamesh
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.73,0:04:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他為了能征服時間而遠離了家鄉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who left home on a quest to vanquish time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,吉爾伽美什尋覓著長生不死的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gilgamesh was searching for immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.57,0:04:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他走遍四方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He looked everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.01,0:04:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,獲得了無上的智慧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}gained complete wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.84,0:04:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,發現了隱藏的秘密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}uncovered what was hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.61,0:04:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他帶著一堆大洪水時代之前的傳奇回到了家鄉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He brought back a tale of times before the Great Flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.69,0:04:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他建造了後世的君王沒有能與他媲美的烏魯克城池\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He built the Wall of Uruk, which no future king will ever match.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.79,0:05:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,吉爾伽美什的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Read the story of that man Gilgamesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.33,0:05:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,描述了一個在烏魯克誕生的英雄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a hero born of Uruk,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.83,0:05:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他經歷了千辛萬苦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who went through all kinds of sufferings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,遠渡重洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Who crossed the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.93,0:05:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,去到太陽升起的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the broad seas, as far as the sunrise;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.87,0:05:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,世界的盡頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who inspected the edges of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.84,0:05:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,只為了尋覓永生的奧秘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}searching for eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.37,0:05:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,在旅途中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On his travels,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.84,0:05:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,吉爾伽美什遇到了一位名為烏特納比西丁的智者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gilgamesh encountered a wise man named Utnapishtim,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.05,0:05:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,智者告訴了他大洪水曾把世界毀滅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who told him the story of a flood that destroyed the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.72,0:05:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,一位神明指示烏特納比西丁\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and how one of the gods instructed Utnapishtim
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.82,0:05:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,造出方舟 拯救他的家人與動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to build an ark to rescue his family and the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.42,0:06:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是世界上最早的關於大洪水的傳說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The earliest surviving account of the flood legend
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.49,0:06:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,它產生於美索不達米亞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was written down in Mesopotamia,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,直到1000年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a thousand years before it was retold
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,《聖經·舊約》中才出現諾亞方舟的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the story of Noah in the Old Testament.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.83,0:06:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,可以這麼說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, you could say Gilgamesh
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.90,0:06:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,吉爾伽美什圓滿地完成了他對永生的追求\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}fulfilled his quest for immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.10,0:06:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是今天的《吉爾伽美什史詩》\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We still read the Epic of Gilgamesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.11,0:06:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,人們每讀一次 他就再生一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and with every reader, he lives again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.08,0:06:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,自從人類第一部英雄史詩誕生以來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And all those heroes and superheroes who have come since
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.51,0:06:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,歷史上還涌現出無數的英雄與超級英雄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}follow in the footsteps of the first hero's journey--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,這可被視為某種形式的永生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}another kind of immortality;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.42,0:06:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,隨人類文明而流傳的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a story sent from one civilization to another
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.52,0:06:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,跨越千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}across thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.86,0:06:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,但生命本身也有自己的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But life itself sends its own stories
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.10,0:06:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,流傳了好幾百萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}across billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.87,0:06:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,它就是我們每個人體內都攜帶的信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a message that every one of us carries inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.97,0:06:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,烙印在我們的細胞之中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}inscribed in all the cells of our bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.74,0:06:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,它用地球上的生命都知曉的語言書寫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a language that all life on Earth can read.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.21,0:07:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,基因的密碼表上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The genetic code is written in an alphabet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.55,0:07:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,只有4個字母\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}consisting of only four letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.15,0:07:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,每個字母代表著由原子組成的一個分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each letter is a molecule made of atoms;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.05,0:07:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,每個單詞由3個字母組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}each word is three letters long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.62,0:07:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,每個生命都是了不起的傑作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every living thing is a masterpiece,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.43,0:07:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,由自然書寫 進化所編輯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}written by nature and edited by evolution;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.60,0:07:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,它的運行與複製\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the instructions for running and reproducing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.27,0:07:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,經由精密的生命機器所操縱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the intricate machinery of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.74,0:07:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,生命的基本信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The essential message of life
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.84,0:07:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,已經被反覆複製了3百萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has been copied and recopied for more than 3 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.61,0:07:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但這些信息從何而來？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But where did that message come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,無人知曉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.99,0:07:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,也許它就誕生於這樣一個陽光照射的淺水塘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Perhaps it began in a shallow, sunlit pool, just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.59,0:07:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,不知何時起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Somehow, carbon-rich molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.50,0:07:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,富碳分子開始使用能量來對自身進行粗陋的複製\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}began using energy to make crude copies of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.10,0:07:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,某些分子變體具有更好的複製能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some varieties were better at making copies,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.97,0:07:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,並留下了更多的後代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and left more offspring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.64,0:07:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,分子間的競爭讓它們變得日益精巧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The competing molecules became more elaborate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.97,0:08:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,進化與生命由此悄然而生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Evolution and life itself was underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.85,0:08:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,或許 生命是源於\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Or life could've started
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.45,0:08:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,灼熱的火山口邊上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the searing heat of a volcanic vent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.62,0:08:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,深藏於海底\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the deep sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.79,0:08:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至有沒有可能 生命是搭著順風車自天而降\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Or is it possible that life came to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.66,0:08:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,來到地球的呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a hitchhiker?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.53,0:08:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我來跟你說個故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let me tell you a story
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.53,0:08:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,關於另一個世界的旅行者的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about a traveler from another world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.04,0:08:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在亞歷山大附近有一個寧靜的埃及小村莊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The peace of the Egyptian village of Nakhla,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.58,0:08:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,叫納卡垃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}near Alexandria,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.91,0:08:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,在1911年6月的某個清晨 突然天降隕災\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was abruptly shattered on a June morning in 1911.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.69,0:08:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,在這塊隕石上記載著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Written in this meteorite was
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.70,0:08:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,來自另一個星球的信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a message from another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.07,0:09:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,但直到70年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But 70 years would pass
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.07,0:09:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,人們才懂得如何解讀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before anyone could read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.67,0:09:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,1976年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1976,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.68,0:09:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,美國航天局將兩艘維京號探測器送上了火星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}NASA landed two Viking spacecraft on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.25,0:09:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾·薩根把我們引向那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Carl Sagan took us there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.85,0:09:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,在人類探索宇宙的早期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on our original journey through the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我們發現火星的大氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We found that the Martian air
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.55,0:09:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,比地球稀薄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was less than one percent as dense as ours,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分由二氧化碳組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and made mostly of carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.22,0:09:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,還有小部分的氮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There were smaller amounts of nitrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.09,0:09:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,氬 水蒸氣與氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}argon, water vapor and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.86,0:09:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,幾年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A few years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.40,0:09:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,當科學家們想要分析\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when scientists thought to analyze the gasses
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.94,0:09:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,納卡拉隕石中含有的氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}trapped inside the Nakhla meteorite,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.94,0:09:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,與及其它的物質成分時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and other members of its class,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他們發現了驚人的相似性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they found a striking similarity--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.21,0:09:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的隕石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the vast majority of meteorites
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.28,0:09:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,是小行星的碎片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are fragments of asteroids.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.55,0:09:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,但落在地球上的這塊納卡拉隕石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the kind that hit Nakhla, on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,只有可能來自一個地方……\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could only have come from one place...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.66,0:10:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是火星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.02,0:10:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,歡迎來到火星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Welcome to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.09,0:10:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,十億年前 這裏的一座火山爆發了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over a billion years ago, a volcano erupted here
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.36,0:10:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,岩漿冷卻後形成了岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and its lava cooled into solid rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.16,0:10:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,幾百萬年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hundreds of millions of years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.43,0:10:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,這塊地方被洪水所淹沒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this area was flooded with water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.47,0:10:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,洪水過後很多年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And long after that flood,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,一塊有直布羅佗岩石那麼大的小行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an asteroid the size of the Rock of Gibraltar
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.50,0:10:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,撞擊了火星表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}crashed into the Martian surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.17,0:10:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,炸出一個大坑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}blasting out a huge crater.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.51,0:10:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的碎片被彈到太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Much of the debris was ejected back out into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.12,0:10:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,碎片一開始繞著太陽旋轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where it orbited the Sun until a gravitational tug
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,直到來自火星的引力把其中一個石塊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from its home planet, Mars, diverted one of the boulders
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.12,0:10:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,轉向與地球碰撞的軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a collision course with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.62,0:10:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,它最終抵達了納卡拉村\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its arrival shook up the little village of Nakhla.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,像納卡拉這樣類型的隕石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Meteorites of the type that hit Nakhla
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.46,0:11:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,就是星際間天然的運輸系統\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are the vehicles of a natural interplanetary transit system
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,它在行星之間輸送石塊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that sends rocks between the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.24,0:11:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,像這樣的隕石可以把微小的"貨物"安全運抵目的地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Such a meteorite can safely shelter microscopic cargo--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是生命的種子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the seeds of life--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.98,0:11:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,它就是星際方舟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an interplanetary ark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.65,0:11:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的岩石是多孔的 有細小的角落和縫隙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most rocks are porous, full of tiny nooks and crannies,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,很適合生命用來偷渡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where life can stow away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我們已經發現好幾種微生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We know that some microbes can survive
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.03,0:11:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,能在惡劣的太空環境下生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the hostile environment of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,比如說 像這些小夥伴們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Take these guys, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.93,0:11:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,這些微生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These microbes spent a year and a half riding
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.17,0:11:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在國際空間站外放置了一年半\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the outside of the International Space Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.74,0:11:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,它們暴露在極端的溫度與真空下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}exposed to the extreme temperatures, vacuum,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,還有宇宙幅射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and radiation of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.18,0:11:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,但它們中的一部分在被帶回到地球之後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And some of them were still alive and kicking
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.38,0:11:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,仍然生龍活虎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when they were brought back to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.05,0:11:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這些生物還有更令人驚異的一面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even more astonishing are these creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.92,0:11:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,它們能從800萬年的假死狀態中甦醒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}awakened from a deathlike sleep of eight million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.69,0:11:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,它們曾被冰封在南極\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were frozen in the Antarctic ice
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.03,0:12:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,在人類出現前好幾百萬年就已存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}millions of years before our species even existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.96,0:12:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,而且它們依然活著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And they're still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.30,0:12:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,如果生命能經受住惡劣的太空環境\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If life can withstand the hardships of space
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.30,0:12:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,並且千年不死的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and endure for millennia,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,那它們就能乘坐著星際快車\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then it could ride the natural interplanetary transit system
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.64,0:12:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,從一個世界到另一個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from world to world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.24,0:12:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,很有可能 我們的微生物先祖們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a good bet that our microbial ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,就是這樣從太空降臨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}spent some time in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.15,0:12:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼我們會如此認為？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why do we think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.78,0:12:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,地球有45億年的歷史\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth is four-and-a-half- billion-years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,在它的誕生初期有一半的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For the first half of its lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,都在被巨型小行星轟炸著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}large asteroids were bombarding the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,劫難每隔幾百萬年就來一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every few million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.06,0:12:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,最猛烈的衝擊可以讓海洋蒸發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The most violent impacts vaporized the oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.93,0:12:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,讓地表的岩石融化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and even melted the surface rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.90,0:12:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,每一次如此巨大的衝擊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each such collision would have
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.97,0:12:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,都能讓星球上的生命全滅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}completely sterilized the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.64,0:12:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,並持續好幾千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.21,0:12:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們從化石中得知\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But we know from fossils in the rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,細菌早已在地球上生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that bacteria were evolving on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.58,0:12:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,從那段地球形成的早期就已開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}during this formative period.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.69,0:13:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,那生命又是如何逃過這些劫難的呢？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So how could life have survived such a lethal series of blows?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.86,0:13:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,任何一次巨大的小行星衝擊地球時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Whenever one of those big asteroids
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,爆炸都會形成大坑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hit the Earth, the explosion would blast out a crater,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.76,0:13:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,將幾百萬塊巨石彈入太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}launching millions of boulders into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.87,0:13:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,許多石頭當中有細菌存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Many of those rocks carried living bacteria inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.80,0:13:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,有些小生物就能像這樣生存在太空中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some of the bugs would have survived in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.14,0:13:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,而它們留在地球上的同類早已被烤焦了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}while all those left behind on Earth would have been fried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.41,0:13:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,撞擊過後幾千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A few thousand years after each impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.75,0:13:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,地球又冷卻下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Earth would have cooled down enough
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.92,0:13:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,水凝聚為海洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for water to condense into oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.42,0:13:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,地球又變得適宜居住了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The planet would again be habitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.22,0:13:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,與此同時 在太空中的大部分石頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Meanwhile, most of the rocks launched into space
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.46,0:13:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,正在繞著太陽轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would have been orbiting the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.33,0:13:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,它們當中的一部分將會重新與地球相遇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some of them would encounter the Earth again,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.46,0:13:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,像隕石一樣進入地球大氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}reenter the atmosphere as meteorites,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.40,0:13:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,將它們攜帶的珍貴生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and deliver their precious cargo of life
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.90,0:13:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,重新播灑到這個行星上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to re-seed the planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.11,0:13:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,如同諾亞方舟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like Noah's ark.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.18,0:13:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,如果生命不能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What this means is that life doesn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.41,0:14:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,像這樣從絕世天劫中重新開始的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to start over again from scratch after each catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,它還能從其他地方再來一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can pick up where it left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.39,0:14:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,當時太陽系還很年輕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the solar system was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.59,0:14:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,金星可能更像地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Venus was probably more like Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.79,0:14:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,有海洋 甚至有生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with oceans and maybe even life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.96,0:14:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,金星 地球 火星都由於隕石衝擊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Venus, Earth, and Mars were all exchanging rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.26,0:14:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,而在互相傳送石頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with each other, due to asteroid impacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.20,0:14:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的生命有沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Does life on Earth carry any traces
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.37,0:14:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,攜帶著這些遙遠的星際迷航的線索？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of interplanetary voyages made in the distant past?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.01,0:14:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼有些微生物能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why is it that some microbes can survive
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.38,0:14:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,在強烈的輻射與真空的太空中活著？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the intense radiation and vacuum of space?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.78,0:14:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,這樣的環境根本就不在地球上存在過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These conditions don't naturally exist on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.15,0:14:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,也許這些小生物在告訴我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe those bugs are telling us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.05,0:14:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的先祖從幾百萬年前開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that their ancestors survived those same conditions in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.29,0:14:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就已經是這樣在太空中活著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a few billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,既然我們知道了微生物能通過石頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So we know that microbes can stow away in rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,在行星之間飛渡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and survive the voyage from planet to planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.86,0:14:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,那有沒有可能從恆星到恆星？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what about trip from star to star--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.37,0:14:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,實現更廣闊的星系旅行？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an interstellar odyssey?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.82,0:15:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,蒲公英\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The dandelion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,有3000萬年的歷史\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Around 30 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.39,0:15:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,它擁有把自身的生命信息傳遞出去的不同方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it evolved another way to send its own message of life
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是通過時空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,每一個種子都是一個小傘兵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each seedling is a little paratrooper,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.07,0:15:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,它漂浮在空氣中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}floating on the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.74,0:15:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,上下浮沉 尋找一個安全之所\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}risking everything for a safe place to land.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.78,0:15:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,上升氣流能把它們帶到高空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Updrafts can carry them higher into the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.15,0:15:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,蒲公英能穿越數十\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A dandelion can travel dozens,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,或者是數百公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}possibly hundreds of kilometers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.65,0:15:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至能跨過高山\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even crossing over mountain ranges.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,進化將它塑造成為精妙的飛行器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Evolution has shaped it into an exquisite flying machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,它的種子就是另一種方舟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The seed is another kind or ark,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,確保物種得以存活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ensuring the survival of its species
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.60,0:15:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,乘風飄往安全之地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by riding the currents of the atmosphere to safe harbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:15:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,每個種子裏的DNA都藏著一個故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each seed in its DNA carries a story,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.47,0:16:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是下一代蒲公英的特徵與命運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the character and destiny of the next dandelion--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.68,0:16:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,生命通過複製自身而傳播出去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}life propagates by retelling its story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.38,0:16:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那生命有沒有可能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Is it possible that life could survive the journey
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.79,0:16:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,在恆星到恆星的旅行中存活下來？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from star to star?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星之間的距離要比\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars are about a million times farther apart
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.66,0:16:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,行星之間的距離多出一百萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from each other than are the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.23,0:16:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,距離是如此的遙遠 以至於要好幾百萬年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Space is so vast that it would take billions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.16,0:16:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的石頭才會抵達那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a rock ejected from the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.03,0:16:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,然後與圍繞另一顆恆星運轉的行星相遇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to collide with a planet circling another star.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.80,0:16:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有微生物能夠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Any stowaway microbes would never survive
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.81,0:16:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在如此長時間的宇宙幅射下存活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the cosmic radiation for that long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.14,0:16:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,但有一個可行的方案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there's a plausible scenario
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.04,0:16:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,可以實現生命從太陽系向另一星系的傳播\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for how life could spread from one solar system to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.59,0:16:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系的恆星受引力的驅動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars of the Milky Way are drawn by gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.99,0:16:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,它們在自己的巨大軌道中繞著銀河中心運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in their own enormous orbits around its center.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.23,0:16:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,比如我們的太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our Sun, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.16,0:16:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,每隔2億2千5百萬年就完成一次軌道運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}takes some 225 million years to complete a single orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.87,0:17:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,在每次繞銀河系公轉中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}During each revolution around the galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽系會穿越2到3個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our solar system will pass through two or three
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,巨大的星際雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}gigantic interstellar clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,每個星際雲都有好幾光年寬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}each of them many light years across.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.75,0:17:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系是一個巨大的星球工廠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Galaxies are world-making machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.02,0:17:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河中有超過100個這樣的大型星雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our Milky Way has more than 100 of these vast clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,氣體和塵埃在那裏聚集\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a place where gas and dust condense
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.29,0:17:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,形成新的恆星與行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to form new stars and planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.30,0:17:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在銀河的旅途中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In its travels through the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.64,0:17:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽不僅由其行星相伴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our Sun is accompanied not only by its planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.64,0:17:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,而且還有數以萬億的遙遠的彗星跟隨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but also by a trillion distant comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.11,0:17:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,當太陽系穿過星際雲時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When our solar system passes through an interstellar cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.45,0:17:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,巨大星雲的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the gravity of the massive cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,牽動了最外層的彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}stirs up the outermost comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.45,0:17:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,有些彗星被扔出到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some comets will be hurled out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.26,0:17:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星間的空間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the space between the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.79,0:18:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,有些則被拉進了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Others will plunge inward...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.60,0:18:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,直奔太陽的路線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}falling towards the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,它們中的一部分可能會與行星相撞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And some of them may collide with the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.86,0:18:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,彗星以高速碰撞了多岩石的行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The high-speed impact of a comet with a rocky planet
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.43,0:18:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,將大量的石頭拋入太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will launch boulders like rockets into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.86,0:18:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,如果這個星球上正好有生命存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If that planet should happen to be inhabited,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.77,0:18:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼這許多的石頭中就會有乘客\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}many of those rocks will carry passengers--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.47,0:18:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,活的微生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}living microbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.80,0:18:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.77,0:18:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,地球石頭的碎塊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}fragments of the rocks ejected from Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.11,0:18:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,會像隕石一樣落在新生的行星上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can fall as meteors into the atmospheres of newborn planets
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.55,0:18:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,就在那星際雲裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the interstellar cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.72,0:19:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,那些偷渡的微生物們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If the stowaway microbes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.32,0:19:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,如果正好遇到了液態水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}should happen to come in contact with liquid water,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.19,0:19:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,它們就會開始復甦並不斷複製\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they can revive and reproduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.80,0:19:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,生命也許就是這樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This may be how life comes barreling
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.47,0:19:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,進入另一個荒蕪的天地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the barren places.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.83,0:19:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽也是由星雲聚集而成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sun emerges from the cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.37,0:19:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,它把生命的種子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}having scattered the seeds of life
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.01,0:19:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,散播在其它恆星的新生世界中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}among the newborn worlds of other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.64,0:19:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,這些新世界現在被生命所觸及\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those new worlds, now touched by life,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.71,0:19:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,然後離開它們誕生的星雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will then leave their birth cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.31,0:19:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,從此天各一方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and go their separate ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.52,0:19:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 這些恆星又會把它們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Eventually, their stars will carry them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.99,0:19:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,帶到其它的星際雲那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through other interstellar clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.42,0:19:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,也許它們又將散播生命到更多的新世界中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where they may seed still more new worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.26,0:19:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,想像一下 如果這樣的過程在不同的星球之間重複\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Imagine this process repeated from world to world,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.73,0:19:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,每一次都把生命帶給另一個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}each one bringing life to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.91,0:19:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,生命就以這樣緩慢的鏈式反應傳播開來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Life would then propagate, like a slow chain reaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.91,0:19:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,佈滿整個銀河\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through the entire galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.92,0:20:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,生命也許就是如此降臨地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This could be how life came to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.95,0:20:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,可我們還不能確定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We do not know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.96,0:20:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,外面是否有像我們一樣的生物？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Are there any beings out there like us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.63,0:20:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,他們是否也在問同樣的問題？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Do they ask the same questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.59,0:20:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,他們也會害怕嗎？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Do they share our fears?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.60,0:20:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他們是否也有英雄與傳奇？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Do they have heroes and adventures?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他們存在 又在哪裏？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If they do exist, where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.48,0:20:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他們又如何顯示他們的存在？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How might they make their presence known?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.09,0:20:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,人類是如何第一次宣佈自己在銀河系的存在？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How did we first announce our presence to the galaxy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.46,0:20:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,1946年 二戰結束後的第二年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was 1946, the year after the Second World War ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.74,0:20:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,再生動的想像力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The vivid imaginations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.77,0:21:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,就算是威爾斯的小說和巴克•羅傑斯的探險\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of HG Wells and Buck Rogers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的瘋狂也比不上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}never cooked up a more fantastic experience
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我們軍隊的工程師\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than the Army engineers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.11,0:21:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,在新澤西州貝爾馬實驗室裏幹的事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at their laboratory in Belmar, New Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.32,0:21:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,它為人類開啟了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It opens up unlimited possibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.32,0:21:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,星際探險的無限可能性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for interstellar experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.15,0:21:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,美國的工程師們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}American engineers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.42,0:21:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,向月球發送了一束無線電波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}bounced a beam of radio waves off the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.02,0:21:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,並成功地檢測到了它的回波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and were able to detect its echo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.00,0:21:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他們把這項實驗稱為戴安娜計劃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They called this experiment Project Diana.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.04,0:21:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,這是由人類發出的首次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was the first interstellar message
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.70,0:21:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,星際信息傳遞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ever sent by our species...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.21,0:21:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一段聽起來很怪異的鐘聲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an eerie, tolling bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.88,0:21:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,只要發揮一下無限的想像力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If one allows the imagination free reign,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.65,0:21:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,無限的可能性會涌現出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}many future possibilities appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.89,0:21:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,載人太空飛船上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Spaceships, carrying passengers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.69,0:21:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,當它以每小時數千英里的速度行駛時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it thousands of miles per hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.63,0:21:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我們能有效地控制它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can be controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.53,0:21:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,並且建立起通訊連接\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and communication established
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.70,0:21:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,與飛船上的乘客交談\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with their passengers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.40,0:22:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,因為現在我們已經知道了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for we now know that the Earth's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.07,0:22:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的大氣是可以被穿透的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can be penetrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.58,0:22:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,物體以光速行進時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Traveling at the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.84,0:22:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,只需要1秒鐘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it takes just over one second
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.18,0:22:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,就能讓無線電波抵達月面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a radio wave to reach the lunar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.92,0:22:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,但擴散開來的波陣面比月球更大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the expanding wavefront is much bigger than the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.85,0:22:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的電波會從月球旁邊經過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the wave passes right by it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.39,0:22:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,只有中央部位的電波會反彈回來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but the central part gets bounced back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.66,0:22:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,經過2.5秒的來回時間後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After a round-trip travel time of two and a half seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.66,0:22:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,電波回到了地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it hits our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.40,0:22:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,戴安娜計劃傳輸了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Project Diana transmitted
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.43,0:22:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,一連串的強烈無線電波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a series of powerful radio waves--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.24,0:22:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,每隔4秒發送1次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one every four seconds--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.67,0:22:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,好比是我們在"Ping"月亮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to "ping" the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.67,0:22:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}ping:用來測試數據包能否通過IP協議到達特定主機
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.08,0:22:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,那些沒有抵達月亮的電波仍會繼續旅行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The parts that missed the Moon are traveling still.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.45,0:22:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,這僅僅是個開端\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.38,0:22:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,二戰後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.95,0:22:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,美國各地的電視台遍地開花\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}television stations cropped up all over the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.06,0:22:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,世界各地也同樣如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and other parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.09,0:22:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,戴安娜計劃發送的信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Project Diana message
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.93,0:23:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,FM廣播、電視與雷達發送的信號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the FM radio, television and radar signals
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.90,0:23:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,在20世紀中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the 20th century
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.36,0:23:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,早已以光速向外四處發送\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all move outward at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.40,0:23:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,這些信號組成了巨大的一個無線電波層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These transmissions make up a vast sphere of radio waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.70,0:23:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,在地球之外向四周擴張\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}expanding away from the Earth in all directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.74,0:23:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,可以說 我們的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You could say that our world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.78,0:23:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,正在向外廣播故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is radiating stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.91,0:23:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先把吉爾伽美什的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors etched the story of Gilgamesh
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.08,0:23:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,刻在泥板上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into clay tablets,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.92,0:23:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,以此把傳奇流傳到未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sending that epic tale into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.89,0:23:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我們則是把故事轉為無線電波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've encoded our stories in radio waves
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.76,0:23:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,發送到太空中去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and beamed them into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.66,0:23:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,它們每年要走1光年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They cover one light-year of distance--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.23,0:23:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是6萬億英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that's six trillion miles--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.60,0:23:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,自從它們被發送出去的那一刻起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for every year of time since they were sent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.07,0:23:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,人類已經像這樣向太空發送信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've been sending our stories into space
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.57,0:23:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,超過70年了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for over 70 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.40,0:23:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,最先發出的電波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The leading edge of these signals
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.07,0:23:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,已經橫掃了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has already washed over
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.77,0:23:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,其它恆星的幾千個行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}thousands of planets of other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.08,0:23:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,如果這些星球上的文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If any of these worlds are home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.18,0:23:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,擁有無線電望遠鏡的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a civilization with radio telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.75,0:23:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他們可能已經知道我們在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they could already know that we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.02,0:24:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,如果其他的世界也能夠發送\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What if other worlds are sending
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.29,0:24:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的故事到太空中 又會怎樣？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their stories into space?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.93,0:24:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,自從1960年以來 人類一直在監聽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Since 1960, we've been listening
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.33,0:24:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,來自外太空的無線電信號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for extraterrestrial radio signals
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.46,0:24:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,不過還沒有聽到什麼像鐘聲那樣的東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without hearing so much as a tolling bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.77,0:24:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,不過我們的研究還過於零散\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But our search has been sporadic
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.47,0:24:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,只局限於天空中的某個部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and limited to certain parts of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.81,0:24:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,現在我們知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For all we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.31,0:24:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我們也許錯過了某些外星人的信號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we may have just missed an alien signal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.98,0:24:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我們找的是錯誤的地點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}looking in the wrong place
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.55,0:24:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在錯誤的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the wrong time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.72,0:24:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我們監聽的只是很小的一個部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've only listened to a miniscule fraction
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.85,0:24:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,對於我們銀河系的星球來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the stars in our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.56,0:24:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,或許還有其他的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And there may be another problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.22,0:24:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我們人類從某些方面來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we are, to some extent,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.06,0:24:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,是時代的囚徒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}prisoners of our own moment in time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.03,0:24:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,受困於我們的科技水平\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the limits of our technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.96,0:24:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,無線電與電視廣播\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Radio and television broadcasting
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.47,0:24:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,也許只是在人類的科技發展史中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}may be only a brief passing phase
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.90,0:24:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,一個很簡單的階段\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in our technological development.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.57,0:24:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,當我們設想著外星文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When we imagine alien civilizations
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.31,0:24:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,也在用無線電望遠鏡發送著信號的時候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}broadcasting signals with radio telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.74,0:24:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我們又和那些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are we any different from earlier generations
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.98,0:25:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,設想著乘坐炮彈飛到月球的先人有什麼不同?\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14} who imagined riding cannon shells to the Moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.98,0:25:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,比人類更先進的外星文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Civilizations even slightly more advanced than ours
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.92,0:25:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,也許已經發展到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}may have already moved on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.56,0:25:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,另外一種通訊模式了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to some other mode of communication,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.29,0:25:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,一種我們還不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one that we have yet to discover
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.19,0:25:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,更無法想像的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or even imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.20,0:25:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的信息很有可能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their messages could be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.76,0:25:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,此刻就圍繞在我們的周圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}swirling around us, at this very moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.53,0:25:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,可我們不懂得怎麼去捕獲它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but we lack the means to perceive them,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.20,0:25:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,就像我們的祖先一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just as all of our ancestors,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.97,0:25:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,在一個多世紀以前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}up to a little more than a century ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.74,0:25:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,人們經常會察覺不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would have been oblivious to the most urgent radio signal
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.94,0:25:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,從別的地方傳來的無線電呼救信號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from another world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.81,0:25:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一個更棘手的可能性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there's another, more troubling possibility--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.98,0:25:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,文明和生命體一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}civilizations, like other living things,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.75,0:25:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,由於自然的原因或者是暴力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}may only live so long before perishing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.52,0:25:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,或者是自行造成的毀滅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}due to natural causes, or violence,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.79,0:25:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,在生存過一段時間以後便會消亡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or self-inflicted wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.13,0:25:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,不管怎樣 我們已經盡力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Whether or not we ever make contact
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.46,0:25:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,嘗試去接觸外星文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with intelligent alien life
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.90,0:25:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,這可能取決於另一個重要的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}may depend on a critical question.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.36,0:25:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,一個文明的壽命有多長？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is the life expectancy of a civilization?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.16,0:26:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,恩西杜拉娜的年代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By the time of Enheduanna,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.67,0:26:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是人類歷史上最早出現借貸的年代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the first person to ever get a writing credit,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.90,0:26:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,當時文明已經存在超過了一千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}civilization was already more than 1,000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.01,0:26:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但今天 她那輝煌的城市只是一堆荒蕪的廢墟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But today, her glorious city is a barren wasteland.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.34,0:26:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,是哪裏出了差錯？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What went wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.78,0:26:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,其中一個重要的原因就是發生在美索不達亞平原的城邦之間的那些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One problem was the almost ceaseless warfare
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.15,0:26:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,無休止的戰爭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}between the cities of Mesopotamia,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.42,0:26:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,摧毀了人類的成就\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which continually destroyed their achievements.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.09,0:26:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,偉大的軍功\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They glorified military conquest
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.25,0:26:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,使它最終成為了犧牲品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and ultimately became its victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.09,0:26:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,另一個消亡的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Another cause of decline
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.16,0:26:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,是他們的技術知識\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was that their technical know-how
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.86,0:26:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,遠遠超過了他們對自然的理解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}overran their understanding of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.33,0:26:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,巧妙的灌溉系統\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The ingenious irrigation system that was the basis
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.04,0:27:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,是美索不達米亞偉大文明的基礎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the great civilizations of Mesopotamia
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.54,0:27:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但也引發了一個意想不到的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had an unintended consequence--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.51,0:27:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,每年水都會經過管道進入他們的農田\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the water channeled into their farmlands every year
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.88,0:27:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,水蒸發後會有鹽留下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}evaporated and left its salt behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.51,0:27:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,經過幾代人的時間後 積累下來的鹽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over generations, the salt accumulated
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.12,0:27:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,會讓莊稼枯死\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and began to kill the crops.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.95,0:27:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,然後 在大約公元前2200年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And then, about 2,200 BC,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.22,0:27:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,就在恩西杜拉娜的時代過後不久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not long after the time of Enheduanna,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.56,0:27:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,災難降臨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}disaster struck...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.49,0:27:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,劫難一樣的乾旱來臨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a drought of truly epic proportions,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.63,0:27:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,延續了好幾十年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lasting for many decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.20,0:27:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,雨停了 莊稼枯萎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rains stopped, crops withered,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.13,0:27:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,遍地是饑荒與混亂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and there was famine and anarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.63,0:27:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,蠻族入侵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Barbarians invaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.47,0:27:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,許多城市的街道上都是死屍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The streets of many cities were littered with dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.14,0:27:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一種解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There could be only one explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.04,0:27:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,恩利爾 至高無上的神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Enlil, the supreme god,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.04,0:27:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他發怒了 因為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was angry because one of his temples
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.65,0:27:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他的一座寺廟被摧毀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.15,0:27:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,美索不達米亞人不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The people of Mesopotamia could not know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.48,0:27:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,同樣的乾旱摧毀了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the same drought was crushing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.22,0:27:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,埃及文明的曙光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the dawning civilizations of Egypt,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.19,0:27:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,還有希臘、印度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Greece, India,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.82,0:27:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,巴基斯坦、中國\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pakistan and China.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.52,0:27:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上所有的神靈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All the gods of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.23,0:27:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,一定是為什麼事情而發怒了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}must have been really angry about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.16,0:27:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管有非凡的才華\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For all their brilliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.60,0:28:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,這些文明中的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the people of those civilizations
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.27,0:28:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,沒想過把他們的經歷與\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had no inkling they were experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.50,0:28:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候突變聯繫起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}abrupt climate change.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.57,0:28:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,3000年後 氣候突變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}3,000 years later, the climate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.88,0:28:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,同樣降臨另一個輝煌的文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would change abruptly for another glorious civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.85,0:28:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,這一次是在中美洲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this one in Central America.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.95,0:28:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,在文明的頂峰時刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At its peak,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.38,0:28:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,瑪雅文明消失了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Mayan civilization perished,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.55,0:28:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,被一系列的乾旱所毀滅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}wiped out by a series of severe droughts
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.05,0:28:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,乾旱延續了一個世紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}over the course of a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.46,0:28:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我們依然記得\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We still carry within us
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.96,0:28:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,這些已經滅絕文明的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the echoes of these extinct civilizations
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.69,0:28:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,留在了我們的語言與神話裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in our languages and our myths.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.43,0:28:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,今天 人類迎來了全球文明的時代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Today, we have a single global civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.37,0:28:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,這一次能延續多久？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How long will it live?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.20,0:28:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,文明的滅絕有很多種方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are so many ways for a civilization to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.77,0:28:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們從這一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's start with the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.21,0:28:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,人類對此無能為力的開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we probably wouldn't be able to do much about.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.45,0:28:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,1000光年外的超新星爆發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That supernova is 1,000 light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.08,0:28:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,它只要再近一點 比如說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If it were much closer, say...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.25,0:28:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,距離地球少於30光年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}less than 30 light-years from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.75,0:28:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙射線就會切碎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its cosmic radiation would shred
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.06,0:29:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,地球大氣的臭氧保護層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the atmosphere's protective ozone layer
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.12,0:29:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,摧毀我們的文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and destroy our civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.33,0:29:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,幸運的是 距離我們那麼近的恆星裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Lucky for us, none of the stars close enough to harm us
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.83,0:29:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,起碼在未來的幾百萬年裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are likely to go supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.60,0:29:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有一顆會變成超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}any time in the next few hundred million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.91,0:29:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,每隔一百萬年左右\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every million years or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.74,0:29:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上會有一座超大型火山爆發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a supervolcano erupts somewhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.48,0:29:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,最近的一次是七萬四千年以前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The last time it happened was 74,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.78,0:29:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,在蘇門答臘島上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the island of Sumatra,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.29,0:29:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是今天的印度尼西亞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in what is now Indonesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.19,0:29:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,它噴出的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It spewed hundreds of times more
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.12,0:29:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,岩石、火山灰和有毒氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rock, ash and toxic gas
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.09,0:29:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,比有記載以來的任何一座火山都要超出百倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than any single volcano in recorded history.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.30,0:29:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,熔岩從地殼中爆發出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The molten rock that erupted from Earth's crust
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.70,0:29:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,離開這個火山口\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}left this caldera,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.60,0:29:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,綿延100公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}100 kilometers long,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.34,0:29:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏現在形成了一個湖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}now filled with a lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.44,0:29:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,多巴火山把超過600立方英里的碎石拋向天空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Toba volcano sent more than 600 cubic miles of pulverized rock soaring skyward.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.32,0:30:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,西風把火山灰帶到了印度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The westward wind carried the volcanic ash over India,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.15,0:30:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,就像一塊厚厚的毛毯那樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where it fell out in a smothering blanket
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.22,0:30:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,覆蓋了整個印度次大陸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}over the subcontinent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.02,0:30:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,這次爆發讓地球的上層大氣充滿了硫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The eruption loaded the upper atmosphere with sulfur gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.36,0:30:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,形成了全球性的霧霾天氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The result was a global haze
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.33,0:30:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,阻擋了大部分的陽光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that blocked most of the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.23,0:30:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,照射到地面 並持續了至少5年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from reaching the surface for at least five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.80,0:30:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像是一個延續了5年的陰天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was like one five-year-long cloudy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.34,0:30:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是所謂的"火山冬天"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This so-called "volcanic winter"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.21,0:30:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,它類似於"核冬天"  但是沒有輻射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}resembled a "nuclear winter," but without the radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.25,0:30:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,全球氣溫下降\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Temperatures fell everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.72,0:30:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是在熱帶地區 動植物都會被凍住\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Plants and animals froze even in the tropics,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.35,0:30:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,死亡的更是不計其數\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}dying in enormous numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.25,0:30:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但生命是頑強的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But life is hardy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.76,0:30:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,只有很少一部分物種遭到滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only a few species were driven to extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.83,0:30:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在印度中部生活的一位古人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One of our ancestors in central India
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.39,0:30:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,就在多巴火山爆發的前1年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sharpened this stone blade
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.83,0:30:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,把這塊石頭磨成了石刀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the years before the Toba eruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.23,0:30:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,而這一塊石刀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And this blade
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.40,0:30:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,是人們發現的十幾把石刀中的一把\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was one of dozens that were found
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.00,0:30:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,它就在火山灰上的那一層土裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the soil layer above the volcanic fallout.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.67,0:30:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,這說明做這些工具的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This tells us that some toolmakers,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.17,0:30:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,雖然他們就生活在直接受火山影響的地區\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even in the area directly affected by the volcano,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.71,0:31:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,依然設法在這場大災變中生存下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}managed to survive the cataclysm.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.85,0:31:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但當時的全球人口\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the global human population
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.41,0:31:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,必定暴跌 然後又出現了回升\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}must have plummeted before rebounding.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.72,0:31:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,如果明天就有這樣一場火山爆發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If an eruption like this were to happen tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.72,0:31:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,即使人類能倖存下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our civilization would be brought to its knees,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.52,0:31:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的文明也會一蹶不振\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}although the human species would survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.03,0:31:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,可以設想 我們的科技在幾百年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I can imagine that our technology of a few hundred years from now
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.90,0:31:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,可以讓我們吸取\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would allow us to siphon off
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.40,0:31:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在火山即將爆發的時刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the energy of a threatening supervolcano
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.44,0:31:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,具有威脅性的那些能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before it explodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.27,0:31:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我們還能把這些能量化為己用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We could then use that energy for our own purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.77,0:31:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,每隔那麼幾百萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}About once every million years, a small asteroid
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.58,0:31:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,就會有一顆小行星碰撞地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}collides with the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.21,0:31:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,造成類似的破壞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}causing a similar amount of devastation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.61,0:31:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,根據我們現有的科技\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With our current science and technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.65,0:31:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,人類已經知道如何避免小行星衝撞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we already know how to prevent an asteroid impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.59,0:31:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我們能提早數年發現它的到來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We would see it coming years in advance
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.65,0:31:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,並把航天飛行器送到那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and could send a spacecraft there
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.29,0:31:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,將它轉移到一個不會造成傷害的軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to deflect it into a harmless orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.59,0:31:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千年後 也許我們的科技\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With the technology of a thousand years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.66,0:31:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,已經發展到能讓我們減輕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we might even be able to mitigate the deadly effects
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.50,0:31:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在地球附近爆發的超新星的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a nearby supernova on Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.43,0:31:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果降臨人類的危險是悄無聲息的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what happens when the danger to a civilization is invisible?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.07,0:32:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人可以預見 那又該如何是好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When no one can see it coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.14,0:32:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,繼哥倫布之後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Beginning with Columbus,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.47,0:32:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,歐洲人不斷侵略美洲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the European invaders of the Americas
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.58,0:32:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,他們攜帶著自己也不知道的秘密武器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had a secret weapon that even they knew nothing about.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.48,0:32:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,就是他們攜帶的細菌與病毒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were carrying bacteria and viruses
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.42,0:32:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,那是致命的疾病 比如天花\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for deadly diseases, such as smallpox,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.55,0:32:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,美洲的原住民從未接觸過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the original Americans had never been exposed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.49,0:32:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,歐洲人總以為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Europeans like to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.49,0:32:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,是他們的勇氣和長槍利炮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that it was their valor and superior weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.53,0:32:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,還有優越的文化讓他們征服了新大陸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and culture that won them the New World.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.40,0:32:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但真正的征服者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The real conquistadors were
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.67,0:32:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是比人跑得更快的病原體軍隊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the armies of the pathogens that raced on ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.93,0:32:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,它們感染並殺死了在北美洲、中美洲、南美洲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to infect and kill nine out of ten of all the Indians
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.77,0:32:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,近九成的印第安人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of North, Central and South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.21,0:32:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,新大陸的偉大文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The great civilizations of the New World
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.01,0:32:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,在入侵微生物的攻擊下崩潰了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}crumbled under the onslaught of invading microbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.51,0:32:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有這支看不見的軍隊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Without his invisible army,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.55,0:32:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,科爾特斯和他的小夥伴們根本沒機會征服新大陸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cortez and those who followed might never have stood a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.42,0:33:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,如果文明走向自我毀滅 又會怎樣？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what about civilizations that self-destruct?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.13,0:33:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的經濟體系是建立在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our economic systems were formed when the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.77,0:33:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,這個星球的空氣 河流 海洋 陸地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and its air, rivers, oceans, lands,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.64,0:33:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎都用之不竭的假像之上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all seemed infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.44,0:33:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他們在人類誕生之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They evolved long before we first saw the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.38,0:33:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,早已走在進化的道路之上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the tiny organism that it actually is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.08,0:33:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,全球經濟體系都有一個共同點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They're all alike in one respect...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.75,0:33:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是逐利而行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they're profit-driven,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.42,0:33:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 只關注眼前利益\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and therefore, focused on short-term gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.65,0:34:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,當代主要的經濟體系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The prevailing economic systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.69,0:34:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,不管它們是姓"社"還是姓"資」"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no matter what their ideologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.19,0:34:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,一律缺乏內在的機制來保護我們的子孫後代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have no built-in mechanisms for protecting our descendants
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.96,0:34:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,哪怕是100年都沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of even 100 years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.99,0:34:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,更不要說一萬年了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}let alone, 100,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.37,0:34:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,從某個方面來說 我們做得比\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In one respect, we're ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.37,0:34:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,古代的美索不達米亞人更偏激\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the people of Ancient Mesopotamia.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.67,0:34:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,和他們不同的是 我們知道自己在做什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unlike them, we understand what's happening to our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.64,0:34:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,例如 人類以地球在過去100萬年裏未有的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For example, we're pumping greenhouse gases into our atmosphere at a rate not seen on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.61,0:34:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,向地球排放溫室氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.12,0:34:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,科學界的共識是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the scientific consensus
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.85,0:34:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,人類在讓氣候變得不穩定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we're destabilizing our climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.05,0:34:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 我們的文明似乎對此又不已為然\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yet our civilization seems to be in the grip of denial;
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.99,0:34:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,陷入了麻木不仁的境地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a kind of paralysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.53,0:34:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,人們知道的是一回事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a disconnect between what we know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.56,0:34:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,做的又是另外一回事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.47,0:34:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,能讓自已的行為適應環境的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Being able to adapt our behavior to challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.17,0:34:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,是人類智慧的體現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is as good a definition of intelligence as any I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.55,0:35:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,如果說高級的智慧是我們物種的標誌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If our greater intelligence is the hallmark of our species,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.52,0:35:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,那我們就應該好好利用它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then we should use it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.02,0:35:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,其它的物種都在利用它們的獨特優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as all other beings use their distinctive advantages--
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.15,0:35:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,來讓自己的後代繁榮昌盛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to help ensure that their offspring prosper,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.59,0:35:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,讓它們的遺傳得以流傳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and their heredity is passed on,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.86,0:35:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,這是自然界的基本體系 維繫著人類的生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and that the fabric of nature that sustains us is protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.23,0:35:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,當然 人的智慧是不完美的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Human intelligence is imperfect, surely,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.07,0:35:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,這就產生了很多新問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and newly arisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.50,0:35:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,人很容易被甜言所惑 不知所措\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The ease with which it can be sweet-talked, overwhelmed,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.40,0:35:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,或是曲從於強權\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or subverted by other hard-wired tendencies,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.34,0:35:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,有時候還會假借理性來掩蓋內心的擔憂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sometimes themselves disguised as the light of reason, is worrisome.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.51,0:35:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,可如果智慧是我們最大的優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But if our intelligence is the only edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.78,0:35:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我們就該善用它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we must learn to use it better.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.42,0:35:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,改進它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To sharpen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.18,0:35:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,瞭解它的局限與不足\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To understand its limitations and deficiencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.52,0:35:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,像自然界的動物一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To use it as cats use stealth before pouncing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.42,0:35:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不濫用它的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As walking sticks use camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.03,0:35:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,讓它成為人類生存的工具\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To make it the tool of our survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.23,0:35:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,如果人類能做到這一點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we do this, we can solve
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.30,0:35:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼在未來的10萬年裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}almost any problem we are likely to confront
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.07,0:36:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,一切困難都能迎刃而解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the next 100,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.04,0:36:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 我們來到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And now we've arrived at the place
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.21,0:36:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,古人夢想中的不朽之地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where our ancient dreams of immortality
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.71,0:36:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,也是現代天文學關注的焦點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and modern astrophysics converge.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.32,0:36:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,巨橢圓星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Giant elliptical galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.42,0:36:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,它看上去有點像佛羅里達州\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are something like... Florida,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.96,0:36:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,在那裏可能有著宇宙最古老的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where the oldest stars in the universe may be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.40,0:36:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一顆紅矮星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is a red dwarf star,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.57,0:36:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,比太陽更小更暗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}smaller and fainter than our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.27,0:36:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,紅矮星是宇宙中數量最多的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Red dwarfs are by far the most plentiful stars in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.78,0:36:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,它與太陽不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unlike the Sun, which is halfway through
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.91,0:36:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽正處於近100億年壽命的中途\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its 10-billion-year lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.91,0:36:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,紅矮星則可以為它們的行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}red dwarfs will continue to provide light and warmth
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.85,0:36:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,提供光和熱超過上萬億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to their planets for trillions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.79,0:36:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,這要比現在宇宙的年齡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's hundreds of times longer
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.45,0:36:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,還要多出數百倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than the present age of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.59,0:36:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,如果智能生命可以永恆存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What would intelligent beings do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.43,0:36:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,他們會做些什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if they had an eternity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.93,0:37:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,來拓展他們對於宇宙的瞭解？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to develop their understanding of the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.26,0:37:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,也許他們能找到在宇宙開啟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Perhaps they would learn how to open shortcuts
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.50,0:37:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,時空隧道的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the fabric of spacetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.67,0:37:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,從而在不同的星系之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to travel between galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.60,0:37:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,以比光速更快的速度旅行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}faster than the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.44,0:37:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,也許他們能創造出全新的宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe they would create whole new universes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.31,0:37:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是藝術或科學的實驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as artistic or scientific experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.81,0:37:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,可現在 至少是在地球上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Of course no one, or at least nobody on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.68,0:37:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人知道永生的人會做什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}knows what the immortals might do.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.68,0:37:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,只要發揮一下無限的想像力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If one allows the imagination free reign.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.79,0:37:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,可我們呢？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.49,0:37:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的未來會是怎樣？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is our own future?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.86,0:37:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的年歷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What would the Cosmic Calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.90,0:37:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,在下一個140億年裏會是什麼樣子？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the next 14 billion years look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.35,0:37:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,如果最初的宇宙年歷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If the original Cosmic Calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.22,0:37:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,包含了宇宙誕生至今的所有時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}includes all of time from the birth of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.72,0:37:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,直到現在這一刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until this very moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.69,0:38:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼宇宙的年歷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what would the Cosmic Calendar look like
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.59,0:38:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在下一個140億年裏會是什麼樣子？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the next 14 billion years?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.40,0:38:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,和過去的宇宙年歷一致\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just as with the Cosmic Calendar of the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.87,0:38:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,未來年歷上的每個月\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every month the future calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.17,0:38:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,都相當於10億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}equals about a billion years;
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.37,0:38:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,每一天相當於4千萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every day, some 40 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.51,0:38:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,科學使我們可以預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science makes it possible for us to foretell
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.38,0:38:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,未來的某些天文事件\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}certain astronomical events
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.41,0:38:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,即使它發生在想像不到的遙遠未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the unimaginably distant future--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.42,0:38:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,例如 太陽的死亡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the death of the Sun, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.72,0:38:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,在大約50億年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In some five billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.12,0:38:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆恆星會耗盡它的氫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our star will have exhausted its hydrogen--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.39,0:38:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,那是它的核能來源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the nuclear fuel that powers it--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.46,0:38:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,成為一顆紅巨星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}becoming a red giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.63,0:38:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,這聽起來很讓人絕望\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I know that sounds depressing,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.70,0:38:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果人類能發揮出智慧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but if we apply our intelligence, our descendants
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.60,0:38:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我們在那遙遠未來的後代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of that distant future will have long departed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.70,0:38:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,也許早已遠離了太陽系這個失落的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the lost worlds of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.54,0:38:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,天曉得\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.38,0:38:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,人類的活動帶來了太多的變數\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Human events entail too many variables,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.41,0:38:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,有太多的不確定性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}too many uncertainties,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.15,0:38:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,很難做出對人類未來的科學預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to make scientific statements about our future.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.71,0:38:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們依然夢想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But we can still dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.82,0:39:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,人類的下一個黃金年代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The next golden age of human achievement
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.59,0:39:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,就開啟於眼前此刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}begins here and now--
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.79,0:39:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,第二個宇宙年的元旦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}New Year's Day of the next cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.76,0:39:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,在最初的十分之一秒內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the first tenth of a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.89,0:39:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,人人都關愛藍色的地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we take the vision of the pale blue dot to heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.16,0:39:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,學習與他人一同共享這個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and learn how to share this tiny world with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.77,0:39:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,最後一台內燃機\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The last internal combustion engine
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.77,0:39:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,被放進了博物館\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is placed in a museum,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.61,0:39:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,人對於氣候的影響變小以至於消失\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the effects of climate change reverse and diminish.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.41,0:39:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在未來的五分之一秒內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A fifth of a second into this future
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.28,0:39:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,人類不再因貧窮而死去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}people will stop dying from the effects of poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.25,0:39:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,地球實現了完全的自給自足\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The planet is now a completely self-sustaining,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.32,0:39:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,成為一個互通有無的大組織\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}intercommunicating organism.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.75,0:39:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,半秒過後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A half-second from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.82,0:39:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,極地的冰帽開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the polar ice caps are restored
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.46,0:39:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,恢復到19世紀的水平\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the way they were in the 19th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.83,0:39:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候將會更加溫和宜人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the forecast is mild and pleasant
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.80,0:39:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,在下一個1分半鍾裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the next cosmic minute and a half--
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.10,0:39:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是4萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}40,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.17,0:39:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,到了人類已經開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By the time we are ready to settle
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.34,0:39:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,向最近的宜居星球殖民的時候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even the nearest other planetary systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.04,0:39:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,世界已然大不同了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we will have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.88,0:39:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,這簡短的一段已然經過了許多代人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The simple passage of so many generations
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.65,0:40:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,人類將會改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will have changed us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.68,0:40:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,自然規律會改變我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Necessity will have changed us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.12,0:40:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是善於適應環境的種族\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We are an adaptable species.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.86,0:40:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不會是像我們這樣的人抵達\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It will not be we who reach Alpha Centauri
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.29,0:40:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,半人馬星座或者其它的恆星星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the other nearby star systems
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.39,0:40:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,乘坐著星際方舟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on our interstellar arks.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.50,0:40:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,那應該是一個很像我們的物種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It will be a species very like us,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.13,0:40:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,比我們更強又沒有我們的缺點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but with more of our strengths and fewer of our weaknesses;
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.87,0:40:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,更有自信 目光遠大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more confident, far-seeing,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.97,0:40:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,更有能力和智慧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}capable and wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.71,0:40:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,雖然我們有種種弱點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For all our failings,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.48,0:40:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,缺陷和局限性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}despite our flaws and limitations,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.98,0:40:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們人類仍可稱得上偉大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we humans are capable of greatness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.71,0:40:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,有什麼夢想在我們這個時代無法實現的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What new wonders, undreamt of in our time,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.98,0:40:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,也會在下一代得以成真\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will we have accomplished in another generation...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.52,0:40:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,或是再下下一代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and another?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.76,0:40:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我們這飄泊的種族\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How far will our nomadic species
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.93,0:40:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,是否還要在下個世紀末\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have wandered by the end of the next century,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.50,0:40:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,或下一個千禧年時繼續漫遊？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the next millennium?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.37,0:40:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我們遙遠的後代們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our remote descendants,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.84,0:40:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,也許能安逸地活在其它的星球上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}safely arrayed on many worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.74,0:41:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,遍佈整個太陽系甚至更遙遠的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}throughout the solar system and beyond,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.37,0:41:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他們將會團結在共同的傳統之下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will be unified by their common heritage,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.74,0:41:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,共同關注著他們的家園\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by their regard for their home planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.21,0:41:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,共同分享著知識\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and by their knowledge that, whatever other life may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.92,0:41:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,不管其它的生命是何種形式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the only humans in all the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.72,0:41:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中只有人類是來自地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}came from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.89,0:41:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他們將會把目光集聚在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They will gaze up and strain to find
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.89,0:41:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,天空中那藍色的小點上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the blue dot in their skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.70,0:41:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,他們會驚嘆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They will marvel at how vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.96,0:41:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我們擁有的潛力曾經是何等的脆弱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the repository of all our potential once was,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.63,0:41:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的早期是何等的險惡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how perilous our infancy,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.54,0:41:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的起源是何等的卑微\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how humble our beginnings,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.64,0:41:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們又跨越了多少的險阻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how many rivers we had to cross...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.48,0:41:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,才找到了這條大道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before we found our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.00,0:41:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,中文翻譯 幸福的微笑 timhal
